=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Prepare the 7-substituted tetrahydroisoquinoline ester core from ethyl 2-(2-bromomethylphenyl)acetate (or the corresponding 2-formyl analogue) by condensation/cyclization with aminoacetaldehyde dimethyl acetal to give the 6,7-dihydroisoquinoline bearing CH2CO2Et, then hydrogenate to the corresponding 1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinoline ester. | Step 2: N-Alkylate that tetrahydroisoquinoline with 3-bromopropionitrile (or Boc-protected 3-bromopropylamine); if nitrile is used, reduce it to the primary amine to give ethyl 2-(2-(3-aminopropyl)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinolin-7-yl)acetate. | Step 3: Reductive amination of this terminal primary amine with 4-(trifluoromethoxy)benzaldehyde (e.g. NaBH3CN/NaBH(OAc)3) furnishes the unsymmetrical secondary amine ethyl 2-(2-(3-((4-(trifluoromethoxy)benzyl)amino)propyl)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinolin-7-yl)acetate. | Step 4: Couple this secondary amine with 4-chloro-2-ethylpyrimidine under SNAr conditions (base, heat, polar solvent) to form the ethyl ester precursor CCc1cnc(N(CCCN2CCc3ccc(CC(=O)OEt)cc3C2)Cc2ccc(OC(F)(F)F)cc2)nc1. | Step 5: Hydrolyze the ethyl ester (LiOH or NaOH, aq. THF/MeOH) to the acid, giving the exact target CCc1cnc(N(CCCN2CCc3ccc(CC(=O)O)cc3C2)Cc2ccc(OC(F)(F)F)cc2)nc1.

=== NORMALIZED STUDENT ANSWER ===
Step 1: Prepare the 7-substituted tetrahydroisoquinoline ester core from ethyl 2-(2-bromomethylphenyl)acetate (or the corresponding 2-formyl analogue) by condensation/cyclization with aminoacetaldehyde dimethyl acetal to give the 6,7-dihydroisoquinoline bearing CH2CO2Et, then hydrogenate to the corresponding 1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinoline ester. | Step 2: N-Alkylate that tetrahydroisoquinoline with 3-bromopropionitrile (or Boc-protected 3-bromopropylamine); if nitrile is used, reduce it to the primary amine to give ethyl 2-(2-(3-aminopropyl)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinolin-7-yl)acetate. | Step 3: Reductive amination of this terminal primary amine with 4-(trifluoromethoxy)benzaldehyde (e.g. NaBH3CN/NaBH(OAc)3) furnishes the unsymmetrical secondary amine ethyl 2-(2-(3-((4-(trifluoromethoxy)benzyl)amino)propyl)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinolin-7-yl)acetate. | Step 4: Couple this secondary amine with 4-chloro-2-ethylpyrimidine under SNAr conditions (base, heat, polar solvent) to form the ethyl ester precursor CCc1cnc(N(CCCN2CCc3ccc(CC(=O)OEt)cc3C2)Cc2ccc(OC(F)(F)F)cc2)nc1. | Step 5: Hydrolyze the ethyl ester (LiOH or NaOH, aq. THF/MeOH) to the acid, giving the exact target CCc1cnc(N(CCCN2CCc3ccc(CC(=O)O)cc3C2)Cc2ccc(OC(F)(F)F)cc2)nc1.

